  "prompt": "Should my quadruplet brothers and I apply to HYS together if we aren't academically similar (test score wise)?",
  "response": "Each of you should apply based on your individual academic merits, test scores, and overall application strengths. While it's great to support each other, law school admissions look at each candidate individually. If your scores and credentials differ, you should:\n\n1. Research schools that best match each of your academic profiles\n2. Apply to schools where you each have the strongest chance of admission\n3. Consider your individual career goals and preferences\n4. Don't assume you need to apply to exactly the same schools\n\nThe goal is for each of you to attend the best law school that fits your specific academic and professional aspirations.",
